data.title: Iceland Beats the Netherlands for the First Time
data.meta_description: Gylfi Sigurdsson scored both goals as host Iceland stunned the Netherlands, 2-0, in a European Championship qualifier.
data.text: Gylfi Sigurdsson scored both goals on Monday as host Iceland stunned the Netherlands, 2-0, in a European Championship qualifier. It was Iceland’s first victory over the Netherlands in 11 meetings. Martin Odegaard, 15, became the youngest player to appear in a qualifier when he came on as a second-half substitute in host Norway’s 2-1 win over Bulgaria.
